│ I propose the following minimal, targeted fix to avoid the miscompile without │
│ perturbing other folds:                                                       │
│                                                                               │
│ - Keep the select-into-op fold generally enabled.                             │
│ - Bail out only for the exact problematic case: self-multiply FMul under      │
│ no-infs when folding select(cond, fmul x, x, x) into fmul x, select(cond, x,  │
│ 1.0). This is the case that Alive2 shows becomes more poisonous.              │
│                                                                               │
│ Patch details:                                                                │
│ - In InstCombineSelect::foldSelectIntoOp, within TryFoldSelectIntoOp, add a   │
│ guard:                                                                        │
│   - If the FP op (TVI) is FMul and has no-infs,                               │
│   - We are not swapping operands (Swapped == false), so the false arm becomes │
│ the identity,                                                                 │
│   - The fold is the self-multiply case where FalseVal == OOp,                 │
│   - The identity constant is exactly 1.0,                                     │
│   - Then return nullptr to avoid the fold.                                    │
│                                                                               │
│ This ensures we do not introduce unconditional 'fmul ninf x, 1.0' for         │
│ self-multiply with possible infinity while still allowing other beneficial    │
│ folds that the test suite expects.                                            │
│                                                                               │
│ Please rerun the full test suite to confirm the fix.                          │
